<subSubSection id="ED41E96542908B6E354300C07C00D926" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" type="description">
<paragraph id="6E40FB01B05E7A1E78CD9D8FB039B665" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
Unterscheidet sich von der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="B84FD190DF5B7390D8DF9ACEDE61A75D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Malva" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="42CABF6602F869D7A90FD6FC52874B95" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Malva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="CB1799F7FE080A0D2842B34C5374CA2C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
<normalizedToken id="C90DAC184E6BB5141C794DD3105FBC05" originalValue="Außenkelchblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Aussenkelchblaetter</normalizedToken>
6-9, gegen den Grund hin verwachsen.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="24B1B8B08D45BB562A9A75D2361E8936" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="0051B2BFC40C504985F02B26F5C207AD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Althaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E590C9DCE3D7CE968273D80EE7B1510C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Althaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="46E76C9121B3521E2C2F5ADDBF92B615" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">umfasst</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="129DEC29D7F2614B4535634836AE6E2D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">etwa 25 Arten</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="075D7FE6D1B45B64F3039D65EB9E21D8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">die vor allem im subtropischen Asien verbreitet sind.</emphasis>
Zytologische Untersuchungen (12 Arten) von Skovsted (1935 Arten) von Skovsted (1941): 
<emphasis id="95C47FB2931CA5D4F355A2873758B739" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Chromosomengrundzahl</emphasis>
n = 7 (2n = 42, 84, 112).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5DAAD0AF45F21E8B67B4AE8D2103D7DE" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
<table id="C0FAA84F6FA92E092646A65BAB1E7F7C" frame="void" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" rules="none" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
<tbody id="994BFCCF7B03EF9905AE1280ADDE835E" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
<tr id="D8B1343C6CCF4ADAC90B4F4D53D86AA8" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
<td id="C151E55ED07185A8285059E317521FA8" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" valign="top">1. Pflanze sehr dicht und weich (samtig) behaart</td>
<td id="6AC8C82F0645C9EBF0904FEECFD7FAE6" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" valign="bottom">
<taxonomicName id="7F6A45C7A2FD56EB5EFDEE1DF8E268AB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Althaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinalis">
<italic id="76E671CB7C809A37A8A9178FDBC8F21E" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">A. officinalis</italic>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 1)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="16D899D5560A382F1854B6BDB023C347" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
<td id="AD4F0175DA7920BD4ACC169D1773DF88" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" valign="top">1.* Pflanze locker und borstig behaart.</td>
</tr>
<tr id="4C5FD399B90D28E6D9AA290791BB1660" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
<td id="492DCC9A46104624337E0D99AA407285" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" valign="top">
2. Oberste 
<normalizedToken id="6428A23CF61C74B877A892A1A4BB4DB2" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
nicht geteilt oder wenig tief geteilt; 
<normalizedToken id="4B48B94968018672EB7157C2649E6BAF" originalValue="Teilfrüchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Teilfruechte</normalizedToken>
auf dem 
<normalizedToken id="9A934AAF76859390052BB06C21477F6C" originalValue="Rücken" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Ruecken</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="1A37B438F86A8BB8195D62543B34453E" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">+/-</normalizedToken>
dicht behaart
</td>
<td id="BD0353466A8771326D51E2792F98ED91" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" valign="bottom">
<taxonomicName id="CD05F232BCE51CD2D181C17738ECEBA3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Althaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rosea">
<italic id="C79A8331E1130557EDB98E24A44C5C17" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">A. rosea</italic>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="A5439DE0853C691A17E793C844CD1F70" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">
<td id="ACECF6DB9CA8654BE5FD7F58B70E74D1" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" valign="top">
2*. Oberste 
<normalizedToken id="7D9BD2FCF3ABFA2FAA50259258B15980" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
bis nahe dem Grunde 3- oder 5teilig; 
<normalizedToken id="ACA14A2D123EB80BB15A59EDF0903217" originalValue="Teilfrüchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">Teilfruechte</normalizedToken>
kahl
</td>
<td id="31C807E41DB4D4B366D8049E05C44A5F" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" valign="bottom">
<taxonomicName id="DE1319B53F4CB5EC7F8F6C39CCDD8935" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Althaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="null" pageNumber="708" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<italic id="450F469552949116E450F5B063E14E02" pageId="null" pageNumber="708">A. hirsuta</italic>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 3)
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</paragraph>
